Class FunctionParser

  • public class FunctionParser
extends AbstractParser<FunctionDefinitionSyntaxAST>
    A AbstractParser for the FunctionDefinitionSyntaxAST with which you can easily parse the FunctionDefinitionSyntaxAST or check if the current AbstractToken is capable to parse the FunctionDefinitionSyntaxAST.

      • canParse

        public boolean canParse(AbstractSyntaxAST parentAST,
                        SyntaxAnalyzer syntaxAnalyzer)
        Tests if the current AbstractToken is capable to parse this AST. It only checks if the current AbstractToken is an IdentifierToken and if it's content equal to the "fun" keyword. Depending on that it will return false or true.
        Specified by:
        canParse in class AbstractParser<FunctionDefinitionSyntaxAST>
        Parameters:
        parentAST - the AbstractSyntaxAST in which this AST is getting parsed.
        syntaxAnalyzer - the SyntaxAnalyzer which is used to call methods like SyntaxAnalyzer.matchesCurrentToken(TokenType) etc.
        Returns:
        false if the current AbstractToken isn't an IdentifierToken which has the content "fun" or true if it is.
